			<ns0:name>k...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112873510090665368075/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Cairo which is in naclports does not use host-supplied fonts. It only works with fonts provided by website.

We should decide what we want to do with fonts in the future. For some applications website-provided fonts are fine (if the apps drive the whole UI), but for some - they are not (if NaCl-constructed image should coexist with browser-rendered text on the same page).

If we don't want to support browser-provided fonts them we should probably remove existing functions, if we do want to support them then we should add more control to make them usable for more usecases.
